President Obama has nominated Kenneth F. Bohac to serve as a United States Marshal for the Central District of Illinois. Bohac has dedicated his entire law enforcement career to the United States Marshals Service and has served in various roles, including as a Deputy U.S. Marshal and a Senior Investigator. He is also a member of the Marshals Service's Special Operations Group and has previously traveled to Iraq in that capacity. Bohac has most recently worked as a Judicial Security Inspector in the Marshals Service's Lexington, Kentucky office. Prior to joining the Marshals Service, he worked as an accountant and financial systems analyst for private companies. Bohac holds a B.A. in Accounting from Western Illinois University and an M.B.A. from Lewis University. President Obama expressed confidence that Bohac will serve and protect the American people with distinction.